Violets and elephants have very little in common. Violets are small flowers, while elephants are large mammals. They live in vastly different environments, with violets growing in the ground and elephants living in forests and grasslands. Their physical characteristics also differ greatly: violets have thin stems and delicate petals, whereas elephants have thick skin, tusks, and huge ears.
